title: Is Antegrade Transmalleolar Drilling Method for Osteochondral Lesion of Talus Necessary? Iatrogenic Cystic Formation at the Tibia: A Report of Five Cases
patient: A 31-year-old woman consulted due to impingement syndrome. Initial MRI showed a 9.6 mm × 10.8 mm talar osteochondral lesion. Drilling of the distal tibia was done using K-wire with surgery lasting for 66 minutes. On follow-up MRI, cystic lesion over the medial malleolus was found without relation to the patient's symptom.
